    * - ``hash-start-block``
      - u32
      - Offset in ``hash-block-size``-sized blocks from the start of the
        sub-image to the root block of the hash tree.
-   * - ``algo``
-     - string
-     - Hash algorithm name, e.g. ``"sha256"``.
    * - ``digest``
      - byte array
      - Root hash of the Merkle tree, stored as raw bytes. Length must match
@@ -218,28 +232,42 @@ The ``digest`` and ``salt`` byte arrays
 Generating verity metadata
 --------------------------
 
-To prepare a filesystem image with dm-verity metadata::
+``mkimage`` automates the entire process.  When it encounters a
+``dm-verity`` subnode, it:
+
+1. Writes the embedded image data to a temporary file.
+2. Runs ``veritysetup format`` with the user-supplied algorithm and
+   block sizes.
+3. Parses ``Root hash`` and ``Salt`` from ``veritysetup`` stdout.
+4. Reads back the expanded file (original data + verity superblock +
+   Merkle hash tree) and replaces the image's ``data`` property.
+5. Writes the computed ``digest``, ``salt``, ``num-data-blocks``, and
+   ``hash-start-block`` properties into the ``dm-verity`` subnode.
+
+Images with ``dm-verity`` subnodes **must** use external data layout
+(``mkimage -E``).  ``mkimage`` will abort with an error if ``-E`` is
+not specified.
+
+Usage::
 
     # Create the filesystem image
     mksquashfs rootfs/ rootfs.squashfs -comp xz
 
-    # Generate the Merkle tree and append it to the image
-    veritysetup format rootfs.squashfs rootfs.squashfs \
-        --hash=sha256 --data-block-size=4096 --hash-block-size=4096
-
-The ``veritysetup format`` command prints ``Root hash``, ``Salt``,
-``Data blocks``, ``Data block size``, ``Hash block size`` and other values —
-use these to populate the ``dm-verity`` subnode in the ``.its`` file.
-The ``Root hash`` and ``Salt`` hex strings must be converted to raw byte
-arrays (``[xx xx ...]`` syntax in DTS).  ``hash-start-block`` is typically
-``num-data-blocks + 1`` to skip the 512-byte verity superblock padded to
-one hash block.
+    # Build the FIT (dm-verity is computed automatically)
+    mkimage -E -f image.its image.itb
+
+``veritysetup`` (from the cryptsetup_ package) must be installed on
+the build host.
+
+.. _cryptsetup: https://gitlab.com/cryptsetup/cryptsetup
 
 .. note::
 
-   The example above appends the hash tree to the same file as the data.
-   This is the expected layout: data blocks followed by a 512-byte verity
-   superblock (padded to one hash block), followed by the hash-tree blocks.
+   The Merkle hash tree is appended to the image data within the FIT
+   external data section.  The layout is: data blocks, followed by a
+   512-byte verity superblock (padded to one ``hash-block-size`` block),
+   followed by the hash-tree blocks.  ``hash-start-block`` is set to
+   ``num-data-blocks + 1`` (skipping the superblock).
 
